article_title: Alibaba Clouds Won’t Clear Just Yet -- Heard on the Street
article_text:
Alibaba shares have taken a beating. But the Chinese e-commerce giant is still no bargain, especially with so many challenges lying ahead.

Alibaba underpriced its shares in the initial public offering in September last year, ensuring a headline-grabbing pop on the first day of trading. The shares remained elevated for a while, but they have sagged so far in 2015, especially after two events in January that spooked investors.

article_summary:
Alibaba underpriced its shares in the initial public offering in September last year, ensuring a headline-grabbing pop on the first day of trading.
The shares remained elevated for a while, but they have sagged so far in 2015, especially after two events in January that spooked investors.
Alibaba shares have taken a beating.
But the Chinese e-commerce giant is still no bargain, especially with so many challenges lying ahead.
